    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-18T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-18T16:00:00-05:00" n="372"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d372">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/659</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-18T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 18, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2279. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 1444. Embassy 2807, October 15, your 1667. Referring to your letter No. 5385,
                    September 12,<note n="1" xml:id="d372fn1">Not printed.</note> the following
                    reply was despatched to you by pouch on October 10: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>The Departments of Commerce and State have prepared the following
                            memorandum which you are authorized to sign and present to the British
                            Treasury: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>With reference to Swedish agreement of May 29, 1918, between the
                                    British Minster of Munitions and the Grängesberg Trading Company
                                    for the purchase <pb facs="0458" n="1292" xml:id="pg_1292"/> of
                                    2,000,000 tons of iron ore, I am authorized by the Government of
                                    the United States to state that on the 29th day of June, 1918,
                                    the President of the United States made an allotment of
                                    $6,000,000 out of a fund available for that purpose to be
                                    expended by the Secretary of Commerce in payment to the proper
                                    authorities of the Government of Great Britain of a one-third
                                    part of the purchase price (together with storage and
                                    transportation charges and any other expense in connection with
                                    the purchase, storage and transportation to the United States)
                                    of 2,000,000 tons of Swedish iron ore, the purchase of which is
                                    provided for in the agreement of May 29, 1918, between the
                                    Governments Of Great Britain, France and Italy and the
                                    Government of Sweden. A copy of the order making said allotment
                                    is annexed hereto. Pursuant to the order, the sum of $6,000,000
                                    has been transferred on the books of the United States Treasury
                                    Department and is now subject to the order of the Secretary of
                                    Commerce for the purposes authorized by said order.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>To this memorandum should be attached a copy of the Executive order referred to
                    which was sent to you by pouch some time ago.<note n="1" xml:id="d372fn2">Not
                        printed.</note> Should you be unable to find copy wire us and we will cable
                    you its text.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
